definition.value: A disaccharide derivative that is alpha-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp in which the hydroxy group at position 2 of the galactopyranose moiety has been converted into the corresponding hydrogen sulfate derivative.
A glycosylglucose consisting of beta-D-xylofuranose and beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose and alpha-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
